<P>Full Text:</P>

<P>It is perfectly futile to spend our time if we cannot have responsive answers to our questions.</P>

<P>[The defendant interposed a few words which were not recorded.]</P>

<P>We can strike these things out. I do not want to spend time doing that, but this witness, it seems to me, is adopting, and has adopted in the witness box and in the dock, an arrogant and contemptuous attitude toward the Tribunal which is giving him the trial which he never gave a living soul, nor dead ones either.</P>

