<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<h2>Associate Justice Stephen Breyer</h2>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=15 SRC="/graphics/ctv/supreme/breyer.gif">
<B>Personal Data</B><BR>
Born:  August 15, 1938, San Francisco, CA<BR>
Married:  Joannna Hare, Sept. 4, 1967<BR>
Children:  Chloe, Nell, and Michael<BR>
<p>
<B>Education</B><BR>
Stanford University, AB, 1959<BR>
Harvard Law School, LLB, 1964<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Clerkship</B><BR>
Clerk to the Honorable Arthur J. Goldberg, Associate Justice, Supreme Court of the United States, 1964-1965.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Teaching</B><BR>
Assistant Professor, Harvard University Law School, 1967-1970.<BR>
Professor of Law, Harvard University Law School, 1970-1980.<BR>
Professor, John F. Kennedy School of Government, 1977-1980.<BR>
Visiting Professor at the College of Law in Sydney, Australia, 1975.<BR>
Visiting Professor at the University of Rome, 1993.<BR>
<p>
<B>Government Service</B><BR>
Special Assistant to the Assistant Attorney General, 1965-1967.<BR>
Assistant Special Prosecutor in the Watergate Special Prosecution Force, 1973.<BR>
Special Counsel, U.S. Judiciary Committee, Subcommittee on Administrative Practices, 1974-1975.<BR>
Chief Counsel, U.S. Judiciary Committee, 1979-1980.<BR>
<p>
<B>Judicial Offices</B><BR>
Nominated Judge, United States Court of Appeals for the First Circuit by President Jimmy Carter, December 10, 1980.  Chief Judge, 1990-1994.<BR>
Nominated Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States by President Bill Clinton.  Sworn in August 3, 1994.<BR>
<p>
<B>Civil And Professional Activities</B><BR>
Trustee, University of Massachusetts, 1974-1981.<BR>
Trustee, Dana Farber Cancer Institute, 1977-Present.<BR>
Member, American Academy of Arts and Sciences.<BR>
Member, American Law Institute.<BR>
Member, American Bar Association.<BR>
Member, Judicial Conference of the United States, 1990-1994.<BR>
Member, U.S. Sentencing Commission, 1985-1989.<BR>
<p>
<B>Recreational Activities</B><BR>
Bicycling, jogging, cooking and reading.<BR>
<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
