<h2>Associate Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg</h2>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=15 SRC="/graphics/ctv/supreme/ginsburg.gif">
<B>Personal Data</B><BR>
Born:  March 15, 1933, Brooklyn, NY<BR>
Married:  Martin D. Ginsburg,1954<BR>
Children:  Jane and James <BR>
<p>
<B>Education</B><BR>
Cornell University, BA, 1954.<BR>
Harvard Law School, 1956-1958.<BR>
Columbia University Law School, LLB,1959.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Clerkship</B><BR>
Clerk to the Honorable Edmund L. Palmieri, United States District Court, Southern District of New York, 1959-1961.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Practice</B><BR>
Admitted, New York Bar, 1959.<BR>
Admitted, District of Columbia Bar, 1975.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Teaching</B><BR>
Professor, Rutgers University School of Law, 1963-1972.<BR>
Professor, Columbia University Law School, 1972-1980.<BR>
<p>
<B>Judicial Offices</B><BR>
Nominated to the United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit by President Jimmy Carter. Sworn in June 30,1980.<BR>
Nominated Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States by President Bill Clinton. Sworn in August 10, 1993.<BR>
<p>
<B>Professional Activities</B><BR>
Executive Committee Member and Secretary, American Bar Foundation Board of Directors, 1979-1989.<BR>
Council Member, American Law Institute, 1978-1993.<BR>
Fellow, American Academy of Arts and Sciences, 1982-present.<BR>
Founder &amp; Counsel, ACLU: Women's Rights Project, 1972-1980.<BR>
