<h2>Associate Justice Clarence Thomas</h2>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=15 SRC="/graphics/ctv/supreme/thomas.gif">
<B>Personal Data</B><BR>
Born:  June 23, 1948<BR>
Married:  Virginia Lamp, May 30, 1987<BR>
Children:  Jamal Adeen<BR>
<p>
<B>Education</B><BR>
Conception Seminary, 1967-1968.<BR>
Holy Cross College, AB, 1971.<BR>
Yale Law School, JD, 1974.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Practice</B><BR>
Admitted to Missouri Bar, 1974.  <BR>
Attorney, Monsanto Co., 1977-1979.<BR>
<p>
<B>Government Service</B><BR>
Assistant Attorney General for the State of Missouri, 1974-1977.<BR>
Legislative Assistant to Senator John C. Danforth of Missouri, 1979-1981.<BR>
Assistant Secretary for Civil Rights, U.S. Department of Education, 1981-1982.<BR>
Chairman, U.S. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission, 1982-1990.<BR>
<p>
<B>Judicial Offices</B><BR>
Nominated to the United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit by President George Bush.  Sworn in March 12, 1990.<BR>
Nominated Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States by President George Bush.  Sworn in October 23, 1991.<BR>
