<h2>Associate Justice Anthony Kennedy</h2>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=15 SRC="/graphics/ctv/supreme/kennedy.gif">
<B>Personal Data</B><BR>
Born:  July 23, 1936, Sacramento, CA<BR>
Married:  Mary Davis, June 29, 1963.<BR>
Children:  Justin Anthony, Gregory Davis, and Kristin Marie.<BR>
<p>
<B>Education</B><BR>
Stanford University, BA, 1958.<BR>
Harvard Law School, LLB, 1961.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Practice</B><BR>
Admitted to the California Bar, 1962.<BR>
Admitted to the U.S. Tax Court Bar, 1971.<BR>
Associate, Thelen, Marrin, John &amp; Bridges in San Francisco, 1961-1963.<BR>
Solo Practice in Sacramento, 1963-1967.<BR>
Partner in Evans, Jackson &amp; Kennedy in Sacramento, 1967-1975.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Teaching</B><BR>
Professor of Constitutional Law at the University of the Pacific's McGeorge School of Law, 1965-1988.<BR>
<p>
<B>Judicial Offices</B><BR>
Nominated to United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit by President Gerald Ford. Sworn in May 30, 1975.<BR>
Nominated Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States by President Ronald Reagan. Sworn in February 18, 1988.<BR>
