<h2>Associate Justice Antonin Scalia</h2>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=15 SRC="/graphics/ctv/supreme/scalia.gif">
<B>Personal Data</B><BR>
Born: March 11, 1936, Trenton, NJ<BR>
Married: Maureen McCarthy, Sept. 10, 1960<BR>
Children: Ann Forrest, Eugene, John Francis, Catharine Elisabeth,
Mary Clare, Paul David, Matthew, Christopher James, and Margaret 
Jane<BR>
<p>
<B>Education</B><BR>
Georgetown University and University of Fribourg in Switzerland, AB, 1957<BR>
Harvard Law School, LLB, 1960<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Teaching</B><BR>
Professor of Law, University of Virginia Law School, 1967-1974.  <BR>
Visiting law professor, Georgetown University Law School, 1977.<BR>
Professor of Law, University of Chicago Law School, 1977-1982.<BR>
Visiting law professor, Stanford University Law School, 1980-1981.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Practice</B><BR>
Admitted to Ohio Bar, 1962<BR>
Admitted to Virginia Bar, 1970<BR>
Private Practice:  Jones, Day, Cockley &amp; Reavis, Cleveland, Ohio, 1961-1967.<BR>
<p>
<B>Government Service</B><BR>
General counsel, Executive Office of the President 1971-1972.<BR>
Chairman, Administrative Conference of the United States, 1972-1974.<BR>
Assistant Attorney General, 1974-1977.<BR>
<p>
<B>Judicial Offices</B><BR>
Nominated to United States Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit by President Ronald Reagan Sworn in August 17, 1982.<BR>
Nominated Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States by President Reagan Sworn in September 26, 1986.<BR>
