<h2>Associate Justice John Paul Stevens</h2>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=15 SRC="/graphics/ctv/supreme/stevens.gif">
<B>Personal Data</B><BR>
Born: April 20, 1920 in Chicago, Illinois<BR>
Married: Elizabeth Jane Sheeren, 1942<BR>
              Maryan Mulholland Simon, 1979<BR>
Children: John, Kathryn, Elizabeth, &amp; Susan<BR>
<p>
<B>Education</B><BR>
University of Chicago, AB, 1941.<BR>
Northwestern University, JD, 1947.<BR>
<p>
<B>Military Service</B><BR>
United States Navy, 1942-1945<BR>
Awarded the Bronze Star.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Clerkship</B><BR>
Clerk to Wiley Rutledge, Associate Justice,<BR>
  Supreme Court of the United States, October 1947-July 1948.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Practice</B><BR>
Admitted to Illinois Bar, 1949.<BR>
Poppenhusen, Johnston, Thompson &amp; Raymond, Chicago, 1950-1952.<BR>
Partner at Rothschild, Stevens, Barry &amp; Myers, Chicago, 1952-1970.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Teaching</B><BR>
Lecturer, Northwestern University School of Law, 1950-1954.<BR>
Lecturer, University of Chicago Law School, 1955-1970.<BR>
<p>
<B>Judicial Offices</B><BR>
Nominated to the United States Court of Appeals for the Seventh Circuit by President Richard Nixon. Sworn in November 2, 1970. <BR>
Nominated Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States by President Gerald Ford on December 1, 1975. Sworn in December 19, 1975.<BR>
<p>
<B>Recreational Activities</B><BR>
Flying, tennis, bridge, reading, traveling.<BR>
