<h2>Chief Justice William Rehnquist</h2>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT HSPACE=15 SRC="/graphics/ctv/supreme/rehnquist.gif">
<B>Personal Data</B><BR>
Born: October 1, 1924<BR>
Married: Natalie Cornell (d. Oct. 17, 1991)<BR>
Children: James, Janet, and Nancy<BR>
<p>
<B>Education</B><BR>
Stanford University, BA, 1948<BR>
Stanford University, MA, 1950<BR>
Harvard University, MA, 1948<BR>
Stanford University, LLB, 1952<BR>
<p>
<B>Military Service</B><BR>
United States Army Air Corps 1943-1946. Discharged with rank of Sergeant.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Clerkship</B><BR>
Clerk to the Honorable Robert H. Jackson, Associate Justice, Supreme Court of the United States, February 1952- June 1953.<BR>
<p>
<B>Law Practices</B><BR>
Private practice in Phoenix, Arizona with primary emphasis in civil litigation.<BR>
<p>
<B>Government Service</B><BR>
Appointed Assistant Attorney General, Office of Legal Counsel, by President Richard Nixon, January 1969.<BR>
<p>
<B>Judicial Offices</B><BR>
Nominated Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States by President Richard Nixon on October 21, 1971. Sworn in January 7, 1972.<BR>
Nominated Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States by President Ronald Reagan on June 17, 1986. Sworn in September 26, 1986.<BR>
