<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<h2>Arkansas and the Death Penalty</h2>

Arkansas allows the death penalty as an option in the following cases:<P>
felony murder<BR>
arson causing death<BR>
intentional death of a law enforcement officer, teacher of school employee<BR>
murder of prison, jail, court or correctional personnel or of military personnel acting in the line of duty<BR>
multiple murders<BR>
intentional murder of a public officeholder or candidate<BR>
intentional murder while under life sentence<BR>
contract murder<P>
The sentence is death by electrocution.<P>
Minimum age for capital punishment: none<p>
Arkansas forbids the execution of the mentally retarded.<P> 
Executions 1930-1976: 122<P>
Executions since 1977: 11<p>

