<h2>California and the Death Penalty</h2>

California allows the death penalty as an option in the following cases:<P>
first-degree murder with special circumstances<BR>
treason<BR>
homicide by a prisoner serving a life sentence<BR>
train wrecking<BR>
perjury causing execution


<P>
The sentence is death by lethal injection.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: 18.<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 294<P>
Executions since 1977: 3<p>


