<h2>Colorado and the Death Penalty</h2>

Colorado allows the death penalty as an option in the following cases:<P>
first-degree murder<BR>
kidnapping resulting in the death of the victim<BR>
felony murder <P>
The sentence is death by lethal gas.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: 18<p>
Colorado forbids the execution of the mentally retarded.<P> 
Executions 1930-1976: 47<P>
Executions since 1977: 0<p>


