<h2>Florida and the Death Penalty</h2>

Florida allows the death penalty as an option in cases of murder, sexual battery of a female age 11 or under by a male 18 or older.
<P>
The sentence is death by electrocution.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: none<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 202<P>
Executions since 1977: 36<p>

