<h2>Georgia and the Death Penalty</h2>

Georgia allows the death penalty as an option in the following cases:<P>
murder<BR>
kidnapping with bodily injury when the victim dies<BR>
kidnapping for ransom when the victim dies<BR>
aircraft hijacking<BR>
treason
<P>
The sentence is death by electrocution.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: none<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 383<P>
Executions since 1977: 20<p>

