<h2>Illinois and the Death Penalty</h2>

Illinois allows the death penalty as an option in murder cases which are accompanied by at least one of 12 aggravating factors.
<P>
The sentence is death by lethal injection.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: 18<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 91<P>
Executions since 1977: 7<p>

