<h2>Kentucky and the Death Penalty</h2>

Kentucky allows the death penalty as an option in cases of aggravated murder and in kidnappings when the victim is killed.
<P>
The sentence is death by electrocution.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: none<p>
Kentucky forbids the execution of the mentally retarded.<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 15<P>
Executions since 1977: 0<p>

