<h2>Maryland and the Death Penalty</h2>

Maryland allows the death penalty as an option in cases of first-degree murder, either premeditated or during the commission of a felony.
<P>
The sentence is death by lethal injection.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: 18<p>
Maryland forbids the execution of the mentally retarded.<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 68<P>
Executions since 1977: 1<p>

