<h2>Mississippi and the Death Penalty</h2>

Mississippi allows the death penalty as an option in the following cases:<P>
murder of a peace officer or correctional officer <BR>
murder while under a life sentence <BR>
murder by a bomb or explosive <BR>
contract murder <BR>
murder committed during specific felonies (rape, burglary, kidnapping, arson, robbery, sexual battery, unnatural intercourse with a child, nonconsensual unnatural intercourse)<BR>
murder of an elected official<BR>
capital rape<BR>
aircraft piracy
<P>
The sentence is death by lethal injection.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: none<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 158<P>
Executions since 1977: 4<p>

