<h2>New Hampshire and the Death Penalty</h2>

New Hampshire allows the death penalty as an option in the following cases:
contract murder<BR>
murder of a law enforcement officer<BR>
murder of a kidnapping victim<BR>
killing someone after being sentenced to life imprisonment without parole
<P>
The sentence is death by hanging.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: none<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 1<P>
Executions since 1977: 0<p>


