<h2>New Mexico and the Death Penalty</h2>

New Mexico allows the death penalty as an option in cases of first-degree murder or felony murder with aggravating circumstances.
<P>
The sentence is death by electrocution.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: 18<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 8<P>
Executions since 1977: 0<p>
<P>

