<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<h2>Ohio and the Death Penalty</h2>

Ohio allows the death penalty as an option in the following cases:<P>
assassination<BR>
contract murder<BR>
murder during escape<BR>
murder while in a correctional facility<BR>
murder after conviction for a prior purposeful killing or prior attempted murder<BR>
murder of a peace officer<BR>
murder arising from specified felonies (rape, kidnapping, arson, robbery, burglary)<BR>
murder of a witness to prevent testimony in a criminal proceeding or in retaliation
<P>
<BR><P>

<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
