<h2>South Dakota and the Death Penalty</h2>

South Dakota allows the death penalty as an option in the following cases:<P>
first-degree murder<BR>
kidnapping with gross permanent physical injury inflicted on the victim<BR>
felony murder

<P>
The sentence is death by lethal injection.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: none<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 1<P>
Executions since 1977: 0<p>
<P>
