<h2>Tennessee and the Death Penalty</h2>

Tennessee allows the death penalty as an option in cases of first-degree murder.
<P>
The sentence is death by electrocution.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: 18<p>
Tennessee forbids the execution of the mentally retarded.<P>
Executions 1930-1976: 93<P>
Executions since 1977: 0<p>

