<h2>Virginia and the Death Penalty</h2>

Virginia allows the death penalty as an option in the following cases:<P>
murder during the commission or attempts to commit specified felonies (abduction, armed robbery, rape, sodomy)<BR>
contracted murder<BR>
murder by a prisoner while in custody<BR>
murder of a law enforcement officer<BR>
multiple murders<BR>
murder of a child under the age of 12 during an abduction<BR>
murder arising from drug violations

<P>
The sentence is death by lethal injection.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: none<p>
Executions 1930-1976: 114<P>
Executions since 1977: 31<p>

