<h2>Washington and the Death Penalty</h2>

Washington allows the death penalty as an option in cases of aggravated first-degree premeditated murder.
<P>
The sentence is death by lethal injection.<P>
Minimum age for death penalty: none<p>
Washington forbids the execution of the mentally retarded.<p>
Executions 1930-1976:  48<P>
Executions since 1977: 2<p>

